Europa League
The Europa League is European footballâ€™s secondary competition, for teams that did not qualify for the Champions League, or those who exited in third place of the group stage. In England, the fifth-placed team of the Premier League qualifies for the competition, while the sixth and seventh placed teams often qualify too. The Europa League was formerly known as the UEFA Cup. The league has been postponed in 2020 for the time being due to the coronavirus pandemic.
